<table><tr><td width=300><center>
<h2>4th Infantry Regiment</h2><br>
</center>
</td><td>
<p>&nbsp;
<p>
<a href="../catalog/newproducts.htm"><img border=0 align=right src="../catalog/images/newbooks.jpg"></a><br>
</td></tr></table>
<p>
<img src="images/expbul1d.gif" width="15" height="15" hspace="13"><b>HISTORICAL NOTES:</b>
<p>
<ul>
This regiment was organized at Anderson in March of 1861.  It fought first ar First Manassas under N. G. Evans where it had 11 killed, 79 wounded, and 6 missing.  In April of 1862, the regiment had 450 men.  If was consolidated into five companies and redesignated as the <a href="unit113.htm">SC 4th Infantry Battalion</a>.  Company B became company D of the <a href="unit170.htm">Palmetto Sharpshooters.</a><br>
<p>
One flag survives in private hands and fragments from a second silk flag are in the SC Relic Room. Dedmondt also describes a third known flag.
<p>
</ul>
<p>
<img src="_themes/sccw/expbul1d.gif" width="15" height="15" hspace="13">
<b>OFFICERS:</b>
<p>
<ul>
<a href="bios/s450.htm#jbes">Sloan, John B. E. - Colonel</a><br>
<a href="bios/m325.htm#csm">Mattison, Charles S. - Major, Lieut. Colonel</a><br>
Whitner, James H. - Major<br>
</ul>
<p>
<img src="_themes/sccw/expbul1d.gif" width="15" height="15" hspace="13">
<b>BATTLES:</b>
<p>
<ul>
Fort Sumter SC (12 - 13 APR 1861)<br>
1st Manassas (21 JUL 1861)<br>
Yorktown Siege (APR - MAY 1862)<br>
</ul>
<p>
<img src="_themes/sccw/expbul1d.gif" width="15" height="15" hspace="13">
<b>ROSTERS:</b><br>
<p>
<ul>
<a href="rosters/4thinfb.htm">Company B</a> - Palmetto Riflemen<br>
<a href="rosters/4thinfc.htm">Company C</a><br>
<a href="rosters/4thinfd.htm">Company D</a><br>
<a href="rosters/4thinfi.htm">Company I</a> - Fort Hill Guards<br>
<p>
</ul>
<img src="_themes/sccw/expbul1d.gif" width="15" height="15" hspace="13">
